{"questionId":"3590993","questionHtml":"<p>State the appropriate null and alternative hypotheses for this <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math>-test.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>(<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math>: population mean recovery time for new remedy)</p>\n<p>(<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></math>: population mean recovery time for old remedy)</p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>:</mo><mo> </mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mrow></msub><mo>(</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>:</mo><mo> </mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>:</mo><mo> </mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mrow><mn>2</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo></mrow></msub><mo>(</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>:</mo><mo> </mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept an equivalent statement in words, must include mean and reference to “<strong>population</strong> mean”, e.g. “mean for <strong>all</strong> patients on old remedy”, for the first <em><strong>A1</strong></em> to be awarded.</p>\n<p>Do not accept an imprecise “the means are equal”.</p>\n<p>Award <em><strong>A0A1</strong></em> for reversed hypotheses <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>0</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>:</mo><mo> </mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">H</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo> </mo><mo>:</mo><mo> </mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>1</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>μ</mi><mn>2</mn></msub></mrow></mfenced></math>.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"3590993","referenceCode":"23M.2.SL.TZ2.4e","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"State the appropriate null and alternative hypotheses for this t-test.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Expected, observed, hypotheses, chi squared, gof, t-test"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}